# UI Encapsulation

- Raw Tailwind utility classes belong only in `src/components/ui/**`.
- Layout primitives belong in `src/components/ui/layout/**`.
- Files in `src/app/**`, `src/components/app/**`, and `src/components/questions/**` must use semantic UI components, layout primitives, and variant APIs instead of embedding utility strings.
- Feature files must not introduce raw Tailwind classes, including layout utilities such as `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `space-*`, `container`, `mx-auto`, or width and height classes.
- Layout primitives may accept only structural props such as `as`, `gap`, `align`, `justify`, `wrap`, `columns`, `width`, and `height`.
- Padding belongs to UI primitives because it defines internal component spacing.
- Margin is a layout concern and should usually be expressed by parent layout primitives with `gap` or dedicated layout APIs, not by per-feature raw classes.
- Visual styling such as colors, typography, backgrounds, borders, shadows, paddings, radii, rings, and interactive states stays in `src/components/ui/**`.

# Touched File Rule

- When you touch a file, you own that file's compliance with this rule.
- If the touched file contains raw Tailwind classes, refactor that same file as part of the task.
- Preserve behavior and avoid visual redesign unless the task explicitly requires it.

# Scope Control

- Keep cleanup local to the touched file.
- Do not start repo-wide style migrations.
- Do not modify unrelated files for consistency only.
- If compliance needs shared styling or layout composition, make the smallest possible change in `src/components/ui/**` and update only the touched consumer.

# Extraction Triggers

- Extract or extend a UI primitive when a `className` has more than 8 utilities.
- Extract or extend a UI primitive when the same utility combination appears twice.
- Extract or extend a layout primitive when a feature file needs `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `space-*`, `container`, `mx-auto`, or width and height classes.
- Extract or extend a UI primitive when feature files introduce `bg-*`, `text-*`, `border-*`, `rounded-*`, `shadow-*`, `ring-*`, `hover:*`, `focus:*`, or arbitrary values.
- Prefer `cva`, layout primitives, and semantic props such as `variant`, `size`, `tone`, and `state`.
